title: The Untamed
creator: Max Brand
description: LibriVox recording of The Untamed, by Max Brand. Read by Richard Kilmer. Whistlin' Dan Berry is one of the most interesting characters in Western fiction. With uncanny abilities he controls a wild stallion, appropriately named Satan, and a ferocious wolf dog, Black Bart. Easy going, Berry proves absolutely unforgiving when physically assaulted by a feared, vicious outlaw, Jim Silent. Seemingly without any emotions, Whistlin' Dan is relentless in his vengeful search for Silent and his outlaw gang. The is the first book in the "Whistlin Dan" series. (Introduction by rkilmer) M4B audiobook of complete book For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

reviews.reviewbody:
Max Brand was the best of Western writers and this, the first story in the Whistlin' Dan series, shows his mastery.  

The reading by Richard Kilmer conjures the spirit of the Wild West, which makes this book excellent company whilst driving the M60 (that's a Mancunian joke). 

TheBookworm (Manchester, UK)

This is a lovely story about Whistlin' Dan, his horse, his dog/wolf and the girl who loves him.

The story contains it's fair share of outlaws and shoot-outs, but is also full of man’s sense of loyalty and honour.

It is read by Richard Kilmer in a clear, measured and thoughtful way. Thank you.
